  <p>&ldquo;Memories can be beautiful, and yet what&rsquo;s too painful to remember we simply choose to forget&quot; (from the song<em> &quot;The Way We Were&quot;</em> first sung by Barbara Streisland circa 1973, lyrics by Alan &amp; Marilyn Bergman.) </p>
  <p>If any readers of this web page have any additions or corrections to the list of OGS teachers, please drop me an email me via the <a href="contact.html" target="_blank"><strong>CONTACT</strong></a> page. Thanks to Christine Cudworth for the correction to Miss Verity, which should read Miss Jessie Morris and who was her auntie. My thanks also to Ron MacKenzie for corrections and additions to the list of teachers and Head Boys / Girls..</p>
